reviewText: I like the intensity of el Cigala and his passionate delivery. I don't like his interpretation of tango as much, but the fusion begins to work when Marconi plays the bandoneon and turns the mood towards tango, the way we understand it today (unlike the original sound of flamenco). Altogether, this is a good DVD to have, and it compensates for being to far fro BA to have being present at the Gran Rex.
I give five stars to this DVD. Diego El Cigala is a fantastic singer and has the very best musicians and songs.

This album is so nice!!! The music is amazing, the voices are extraordinary.
I highly recommend this disc, don't miss it!!!
Excellent!!!  Any person that likes good music, should have this as part of his/her collection. The musicians are as awsome as the singer, which enhance the quality of this music production.

Cigala & Tango: Gran RexThe main purpose here is to forewarn other potential buyers that this is a standard dvd, NOT a Blu Ray even though the picture in the advertising shows a blu ray box. However, I have other Cigala products and trust that the music contained herein is equally fine. I have yet to open the sealed box and play it. The only other reviewer gave it a 5 (via Spanish), so that is probably accurate. My lower rating reflects my great disappointment at the misleading advertising. I am sure the defendant would hide behind the fact that the text in the ad refers to DVD. My guess is that 9 out of 10 people are under the impression that Blu Ray is a type of DVD and would thus fall victim to the trap laid by the use of a blu ray box in the advertisement. I only paid $12.57 plus s&h for it, so I'll just keep it.

Este dvd es de la mejor calidad, y los musicos son maravillosos!  Voy a mostrarlo a mis alumnos de niveles 3 y 4.  Muestra una fusion muy interesante de dos estilos de musica:  el flamenco y el tango.  (No puedo escribir los acentos con mi telefono)
